{"title":"Blix Packa Genie adds Affordable Electric Cargo Bike, Updates eBike Lineup","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/14/blix-updates-ebike-lineup/","date":1626266504000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Santa Cruz’s Blix, claimed to be one of the fastest-growing ebike companies in the US, announced multiple updates today. Changes are on deck for commuter, cruiser, cargo, and folding ebikes, with a focus on increased power and range and improved rider experience. Notably, the new Packa Genie cargo model competes with similar entries from a lower price point.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x254/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"786\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-297x156.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-800x419.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-120x63.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-768x402.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-696x365.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-1068x560.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-802x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 802w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x254/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" ezoid=\"0.8783766711569632\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-297x156.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-800x419.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-120x63.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-768x402.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-696x365.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-1068x560.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13133748/Blix_Packa_Genie-802x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 802w\"></p><p>The updates come on the heels of a successful year for Blix. Despite COVID-19, the company grew its teams by 300% in 2020 and, according to its PR department, shipped more orders than it did during its first 6 years combined.</p><h2>The New Packa Genie</h2><p>Blix positions the new Packa Genie as a “natural car replacement” for commuters, with an 80-mile range, 750w hub motor and hydraulic disc brakes. Modular racks and updated trailer mounts substantiate the ebike’s cargo capacity. An integrated head unit makes information readily available, and integrated front and rear LEDs provide road safety.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1.jpg\" alt=\"blix packa genie front light\" width=\"957\" height=\"645\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1.jpg 957w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-297x200.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-800x539.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-120x81.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-768x518.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-696x469.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-623x420.jpg 623w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 957px) 100vw, 957px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1.jpg 957w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-297x200.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-800x539.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-120x81.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-768x518.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-696x469.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154213/Packa_Carousel_4_1200x1-623x420.jpg 623w\"></p><p>The rack system is rated for 200 pounds, and Blix claims that it’s capable of an impressive 200 configurations. The motor puts out 1350w of peak output for hill climbing, and the dual battery system delivers 1228Wh of charge. Various rider comfort features are in place, including a handlebar throttle, auto cutoff switch for braking, and a USB charging port in the head unit.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x.jpg\" alt=\"blix packa genie hub motor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13153845/Packa_Carousel_3_1200x-630x420.jpg 630w\"></p><p>But in promoting the Packa Genie, Blix leads with its price tag: it starts at MSRP $1700, which is competitive in the cargo ebike arena. Interested parties should note that no $1700 option was available on Blix’s website as of this writing. It is possible (though unverified) that $1700 is the price for the single battery iteration, which would reduce the Genie’s range.</p><p>When it comes to electric cargo bikes, this is one of the most affordable that we’re aware of – with the next closest being the RadPower RadWagon 4 at $1,899 (though it has a higher 350lb cargo capacity).</p><h2>Updates Across the Blix eBike Lineup</h2><p>The Packa Genie appears to get the most extensive overhaul as well as the lion’s share of publicity among Blix’s new bikes. But the changes do not start and end with it. The company notes that it also makes the following updates to the rest of its lineup:</p><p><b>Sol Eclipse –&nbsp;</b>Electric cruiser bike, MSRP $1600</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154501/Blix_SolEclipse_Seafoam_1_1400x.progressive.jpg\" alt=\"blix sol eclipse\" width=\"1015\" height=\"834\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154501/Blix_SolEclipse_Seafoam_1_1400x.progressive.jpg 1015w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154501/Blix_SolEclipse_Seafoam_1_1400x.progressive-297x244.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154501/Blix_SolEclipse_Seafoam_1_1400x.progressive-800x657.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154501/Blix_SolEclipse_Seafoam_1_1400x.progressive-120x99.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13154501/Blix_SolEclipse_Seafoam_1_1400x.progr